Living in the rv was always our temporary solution to a very common problem for a lot of working families. 
.
I don’t want y’all to think that just because we may stop living in an RV that there’s something wrong with living this way. We didn’t know how long we would be doing it, but it was a way we could always be together. We both couldn’t imagine living apart.. as soon as we got married in 2013 we moved into a 27ft travel trailer together. Home was wherever we were together.
.
After having the kids Derrick working 6 sometimes 7 days a week if he traveled for work we would have never seen him. Our Rv has made bedtimes special and Derrick present in our daily lives. (I will never forget and always cherish that.)
.
It’s so special not only being able to be together, but having a space that is constant for our kids. We’ve moved 14 times in 10 years… and our kids have had the same bedroom their whole lives and that is what we wanted. 
.
There are many seasons of life, and we have found the beauty and joy in this one. 
.
.
.

What house hunting looks like after living tiny for 10 years? 
.
A little different then you may think. We have this amazing gift of minimalism, that happened by complete accident living tiny. Now after adopting these habits and living in such a small space we look at home buying with fresh eyes. 
.
We’re excited, but cautious… the change will be huge for our family. We still plan on carrying all our minimalist habits with us into a new home. We don’t plan on completely filling a huge house. We love having a neat space where everything has a place. The windows will continue to let in natural sunlight I love so much. The plants may even be real instead of faux…🪴 
.
Either way we are excited to start hunting for a new home. 
☀️Do you think we will go big or stay small?
☀️What will our style look like? 
☀️What will happen to the RV?
.
#househunting #livingtiny #rvlife #rvrenovation #rvliving #livingroomdecor #livingroomdesign

Recipe ⬇️

2.5c hot water 
1/3c olive oil
1/3c honey or sugar
1 Tbsp salt
5c Bread flour
1.5 Tbsp yeast
.
🍞 Whisk water, oil, honey, salt
🍞add 3/4c flour and whisk
🍞Whisk in yeast
🍞let sit 15 min until bubbly
🍞With dough hook, add 1c flour at a time until 5 C. test consistency (sticky, but doesn’t stick to fingers)
🍞Knead for 5 min
🍞let rise in oiled, covered, bowl for 30 min or doubled in size.
🍞Split dough into 2-4 equal pieces
🍞Roll each into a long rectangle and roll up tightly.
🍞Pinch Seals and Place in oiled loaf pans
🍞proof @ 120 covered to rise + fill pan 
🍞Cut slit into top before baking
🍞Bake @ 350 for 30 min
🍞Remove from loaf pan to cool 
🍞Butter tops and wait til cool to slice … enjoy 
.
I’ll usually freeze one and eat the other.. in my house each loaf is good for 3 days before it starts to get crumbly. Also makes great croutons/ bread crumbs. 
.

Original recipe from @katielehuta 
.

Texas Cowboy Stew
.
2lbs ground beef
5 sausage links
1 onion
4 medium potatoes
1 can black beans (drained)
1 can corn (drained)
2 cans diced tomatoes & green chilis (liquid)
2 cans crushed tomatoes (liquid)
2 tsp cumin
2 tsp chili powder
2 tsp miced garlic
Salt and pepper
3 cups water
.
Sauté onion, steam (1/2 way cooked) sausage and potatoes… then add to crockpot. Cook ground beef then add.
Pour into crockpot and add all veggies and seasonings. Combine well. Add 3 cups of water.
.
Cook on high for 4 hours. 🤠
.
.
Enjoy with cheese.. adding rolls next time. ✨
.
.
.

4 tablespoons brown sugar

.

When I couldn’t go to the gym or have time to workout with small kids.. I worked on the one thing I could control: what I was eating. I switched my diet to mostly whole foods and eating processed foods only on the weekends. Doing this helped set an amazing foundation when I added body weight exercise and now weight lifting. 
.
When you jump into the gym and start exercising then try to eat less.. your body will literally hate you. When you expend more energy your body needs more fuel (food).. so being overweight and trying to exercise you will end up actually gaining more weight. Work on your eating habits first. This will give you the biggest impact and the most success for a long term lifestyle change. (This was over a 4 year period) ♥️
.
.
If you’re the goal setting kind… this new years think about the thing you can control and change. Eating is a little thing that makes a HUGE impact not only on your appearance but your overall health and wellness. 😊
.
.
